\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Binary fuse filter with 16-entry array, 2-entry segments, and 3-bit fingerprints. Vertical bars mark segment boundaries. The filter contains keys $\colorbox {lightorange}{$\displaystyle x$}$, $\colorbox {lightred}{$\displaystyle y$}$, $\colorbox {lightpink}{$\displaystyle w$}$ and $\colorbox {lightpurple}{$\displaystyle z$}$, with fingerprints $\colorbox {lightorange}{$\displaystyle 100$}$, $\colorbox {lightred}{$\displaystyle 011$}$, $\colorbox {lightpink}{$\displaystyle 110$}$ and $\colorbox {lightpurple}{$\displaystyle 111$}$, respectively. Entries hashed to by keys are marked with arrows and the keys' colors. Each key hashes to three consecutive segments.}}{1}{}\protected@file@percent }
